comments.body:
If you installed using the .deb package, normal Linux .deb uninstallation instructions should apply. http://askubuntu.com/questions/22200/how-to-uninstall-a-deb-package

@MaximoTrinidad - does `sudo apt-get remove powershell` not work for uninstalling powershell? 

As far as OSX goes, there is no default package manager that I'm aware of for uninstallation, it will need to be manually uninstalled.
